How To Convert Any Face Wash Into A Brightening Powerhouse!

The Secret Mix: Masoor Dal + Besan = Instant Glow

Masoor Dal helps to

- Natural exfoliant that gently removes dead skin cells
- Rich in proteins that nourish and firm the skin
- Contains antioxidants that fight free radicals
- Helps reduce pigmentation and dark spots
- Improves skin texture and smoothness

Besan helps to - 

- Deep cleanses pores and removes excess oil
- Natural bleaching agent for skin brightening
- Tightens skin and reduces appearance of pores
- Anti-inflammatory properties soothe irritated skin
- Rich in zinc and vitamins for healthy skin

And..when used together 

✅ Enhanced brightening effect
✅ Gentle exfoliation without harsh scrubbing
✅ Deep pore cleansing
✅ Even skin tone
✅ Natural glow boost
✅ Reduced dark spots and pigmentation

How to make it

1. Grind masoor dal into fine powder
1. Mix equal parts masoor dal powder + besan
1. Store in airtight container

How to use 

- Take your regular face wash in palm
- Add 1/2 teaspoon of the powder mix
- Mix together until well combined
- Gently massage on damp face for 1-2 minutes
- Rinse with water

P.s.

- Start with small amounts to test skin sensitivity
- Use consistently for 2-3 weeks to see visible results
- Perfect for all skin types, especially dull and uneven skin
- Store powder mix away from moisture

Let me know if you have doubts in the comments!

DIY Herbal Glow Toner -  Made with just 6 kitchen ingredients! ✨🌿 

No cooking required - just warm water magic!

How to Make:

Mix 1 tsp each: green tea leaves, rolled oats, dried hibiscus, dried rose petals
Add 5-7 cloves and one cinnamon
Pour 1 cup warm (not boiling) water over mixture
Steep for 15-20 minutes
Strain through fine mesh or cheesecloth or a strainer
Store in clean bottle in fridge (use within 7-10 days)

How to Use:

Cleanse face first
Apply with cotton pad or spray bottle
Gently pat into skin, avoiding eye area
Follow with moisturizer
Use 1-2x daily (start with once to test sensitivity)
Always patch test first, especially due to cinnamon and cloves

Caution: Start slow if you have sensitive skin - the cinnamon and cloves can be potent!

✨ PERFECT FOR:

Oily & combination skin
Acne-prone skin
Dull, tired complexion
Large pores
Sensitive skin (patch test first!)

BENEFITS:

Controls excess oil
Fights acne bacteria
Brightens & evens skin tone
Gentle natural exfoliation
Tightens pores
Anti-aging antioxidants
Soothes inflammation
Boosts natural glow

Yesterday was grandads 90th birthday! And what a day! 

I remember when me and my brother were younger and I used to go there and every morning I used to wake up to my grandpa and my brother singing rhymes for me.

And then he used to tell us stories with a moral and always made sure we were involved in games or just doing something productive.

Most of us have vivid and random memories with our grandparents - and what I have learnt is ofc you need to spend time with your loved ones- but also TAKE PICS! Otherwise you will end up forgotten them or like small moments and things that happened that day…

And then years later you can sit with your family and walk through those times together ♥️

Part 2 - DIY Hyaluronic Acid Serum At Home! 

If you have been wanted a Hyaluronic Acid serum without spending a fortune - I got you!!

This serum which HOMEMADE is such a delight and you absolutely need to try this if you have used and liked, or, wanted to try out the one from Ordinary 

Recipe - 

90g water 
1/4 tsp glycerin 
1/8tsp hyaluronic acid powder 
Half of 1/16tsp niacinamide powder 

Mix it all together in a container. 

Keep it in the fridge for 3-5 hours. Keep stirring at intervals of 40-50 mins.

Remove it in a glass bottle and store in the fridge for upto a month! 

Comment ‘Hyaluronic Acid’ or ‘link’ and I’ll share the links to purchase the raw materials like the bottle I used and hyaluronic acid!

Homemade Botanical Hair Regenerative Complex Recipe!

And trust me it’s much easier to make than the name!

Recipe:

Rosemary 4 tbsp
Lavender 2 tsp
Cloves 15-20 cloves
Cinnamon 1 pinky finger size cinnamon
500 ml water

Boil the mixture for 15-20 mins.

Let it cool down and then remove it in a glass bottle and stor in the fridge for 4 weeks.

Apply it on your scalp and hair and let it stay overnight or for 6-7 hours atleast.
